  <bioghist id="aspace_e82ad6652df34204a11f16893bb7e1fc">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Senior Extension Associate in the Family Life Development Center, Cornell University.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_16638c103bd68fb2d55ae245492c6bc1">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Curriculum and conference material, correspondence, reports, project proposals, films, and publications concerning work done in the Family Life Development Center (FLDC) concerning child abuse and neglect, specifically ACT (Assets Coming Together) for Youth, a project of the New York State Dept. of Health; the Community Lifelines Program; Statewide Teamwork for Abused Runaways (STAR); and reports written by Barry for the United States Advisory Board on Child Abuse and Neglect. Includes two films, "Child Abuse: A Total Treatment Perspective" and "Child Abuse: Perspective on Being a Parent".</p>  </scopecontent>
  <relatedmaterial id="aspace_6c86692a108b81d93f1399d0e4e4d429">
    <head>Related Materials</head>
<p>"Child Abuse: Perspective on Being a Parent" and "Child Abuse: A Total Treatment Perspective in box 30 (collection #21/36/2566)</p>  </relatedmaterial>
